Although  UBXN-2 is a phosphoprotein (http://www.phosphopep.org/),  the kinase(s) that phosphorylates UBXN-2 is unknown and  CDK1 consensus phosphorylation sites are absent, suggesting  that other mechanisms or other mitotic kinases may regulate the  function of UBXN-2 in C. elegans  embryos.
